{
  "texts": [
    "Early FL techniques use Defects4J v1.2, primarily evaluating against six projects within it.",
    "Recent work employs Defects4J v2.0, which includes more open-source projects.",
    "Additionally, the BEARS [535] benchmark and nanoxml from the SIR [536] dataset are also employed.In C, some C programs from the SIR dataset, as well as the ManyBugs [537] dataset, are more frequently used.",
    "Existing DLFL research has utilized programs like space from the SIR dataset, as well as python, gzip, libtiff, and others from the ManyBugs dataset.",
    "Challenges and opportunitiesThis subsection summarizes the challenges and highlights opportunities for future work in fault localization."
  ]
}